page.title: 03RAIL TRANSPORT IN W.THURROCK
page.content: There are two railway lines passing through the area,both part of British Rail Eastern Region. The main line runs east to west, terminating at Shoeburyness in the east and Fenchurch Street Station, London,in the west.The branch line goes to Upminster from Tilbury Riverside. There are no stations within the area,although Purfleet is just to the west and Grays to the east. The lines carry electric commuter trains(overhead electric cables) and diesal freight and oil trains from Tilbury Docks and the refineries.
